  "text": "No episode of ventricular tachyarrhythmia has recurred in any of the patients to date, which is striking given the high number of episodes of VTs. This finding, however, is in line with the benign course of patients once they have survived the electrical storm. [CITATION_1] This may indicate that in these patients, the triggering fibers finally die because of ischemia or regain normal function. Because antiarrhythmic drug therapy with amiodarone and sympathetic blockade leaves some patients unstable, or the time to stabilization may be prolonged, especially with amiodarone, [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] catheter ablation of the triggering VPBs should be used as a bailout therapy in patients with an electrical storm after MI.",
